# Zyra Production Deployment Checklist

## Pre-Deployment

### Code Quality
- [ ] All tests passing (unit, integration, e2e)
- [ ] Code review completed
- [ ] Security scan completed
- [ ] Performance testing completed
- [ ] No critical or high-severity issues open

### Database
- [ ] Database migrations tested in staging
- [ ] Backup of production database taken
- [ ] Rollback scripts prepared

### Configuration
- [ ] Environment variables updated
- [ ] Feature flags configured
- [ ] Third-party service credentials verified
- [ ] SSL certificates valid and not expiring soon

### Documentation
- [ ] API documentation updated
- [ ] Release notes prepared
- [ ] User documentation updated if needed

## Deployment

### Process
- [ ] Notify team of deployment start
- [ ] Enable maintenance mode if needed
- [ ] Deploy database migrations
- [ ] Deploy application updates
- [ ] Run smoke tests
- [ ] Verify all services healthy
- [ ] Disable maintenance mode

### Verification
- [ ] Critical user flows working
- [ ] Monitoring dashboards show normal activity
- [ ] Error rates within acceptable thresholds
- [ ] Performance metrics within expected ranges

## Post-Deployment

### Monitoring
- [ ] Watch error rates for 1 hour
- [ ] Monitor performance for unusual patterns
- [ ] Check user feedback channels

### Communication
- [ ] Notify team of successful deployment
- [ ] Announce to users if visible changes
- [ ] Update status page

### Documentation
- [ ] Document any issues encountered
- [ ] Update runbooks if needed
- [ ] Schedule retrospective if necessary